prepared in accordance with IFRS. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Please refer to <I>Explanations of Non-IFRS Measures</I> online

from expectations. The factors that could affect SAP&#146;s future financial results are discussed more fully in SAP&#146;s filings with the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission (the &#147;SEC&#148;), including SAP&#146;s most recent Annual

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><A NAME="ex99_1809535_1"></A>Introductory Notes </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">This interim group report meets the requirements of German Accounting Standard No.&nbsp;16 &#147;Zwischenberichterstattung&#148; (DRS 16). We prepared the
financial data in the Quarterly Financial Statements (Unaudited) section for SAP SE and its subsidiaries in accordance with International Financial Reporting Standards (IFRS). In doing so, we observed the IFRS (including the interpretations by the
IFRS Interpretations Committee (IFRIC)) both as issued by the International Accounting Standards Board (IASB) and as endorsed by the European Union (EU). This does not apply to numbers expressly identified as non-IFRS. For additional IFRS and
non-IFRS information, see the Supplementary Financial Information (Unaudited) section. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">This quarterly financial report updates our
consolidated financial statements 2013, presents significant events and transactions of the third quarter 2014 and the first nine of 2014, and updates the forward-looking information contained in our Management Report 2013. Both the 2013
consolidated financial statements and the 2013 Management Report are part of our 2013 Integrated Report which is available at www.sapintegratedreport.de. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">All of the information in this interim group report is unaudited. This means the information has been subject neither to any audit nor to any review by an independent auditor. </FONT></P>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><A NAME="ex99_1809535_2"></A>INTERIM MANAGEMENT REPORT </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>GENERAL INFORMATION </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Forward-Looking
Statements </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">This quarterly financial report contains forward-looking statements and information based on the beliefs of, and assumptions
made by, our management using information currently available to them. Any statements contained in this report that are not historical facts are forward-looking statements as defined in the U.S. Private Securities Litigation Reform Act of 1995. We
have based these forward-looking statements on our current expectations, assumptions, and projections about future conditions and events. As a result, our forward-looking statements and information are subject to uncertainties and risks, many of
which are beyond our control. If one or more of these uncertainties or risks materializes, or if management&#146;s underlying assumptions prove incorrect, our actual results could differ materially from those described in or inferred from our
forward-looking statements and information. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">We describe these risks and uncertainties in the Risk and Opportunity Management section,
respectively in the there-mentioned sources. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The words &#147;aim,&#148; &#147;anticipate,&#148; &#147;assume,&#148; &#147;believe,&#148;
&#147;continue,&#148; &#147;could,&#148; &#147;counting on,&#148; &#147;development,&#148; &#147;is confident,&#148; &#147;estimate,&#148; &#147;expect,&#148; &#147;forecast,&#148; &#147;future trends,&#148; &#147;guidance,&#148; &#147;intend,&#148;
&#147;may,&#148; &#147;might,&#148; &#147;outlook,&#148; &#147;plan,&#148; &#147;project,&#148; &#147;predict,&#148; &#147;seek,&#148; &#147;should,&#148; &#147;strategy,&#148; &#147;want,&#148; &#147;will,&#148; &#147;would,&#148; and similar
expressions as they relate to us are intended to identify such forward-looking statements. Such statements include, for example, those made in the Operating Results section, the Risk and Opportunity Management section, our Forecast for SAP, and
other forward-looking information appearing in other parts of this quarterly financial report. To fully consider the factors that could affect our future financial results, both our 2013 Integrated Report and Annual Report on Form 20-F for
December&nbsp;31, 2013, should be considered, as well as all of our other filings with the Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC). Readers are cautioned not to place undue reliance on these forward-looking statements, which speak only as of the
date specified or the date of this report. Except where legally required, we undertake no obligation to publicly update or revise any forward-looking statements as a result of new information that we receive about conditions that existed upon
issuance of this report, future events, or otherwise unless we are required to do so by law. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Statistical Data </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">This report includes statistical data about the IT industry and global economic trends that comes from information published by sources including
International Data Corporation (IDC), a provider of market information and advisory services for the information technology, telecommunications, and consumer technology markets; the European Central Bank (ECB); and the International Monetary Fund
(IMF). This type of data represents only the estimates of IDC, ECB, IMF or the other mentioned sources of industry data. SAP does not adopt or endorse any of the statistical information. In addition, although we believe that data from these sources
is generally reliable, this type of data is imprecise. We caution readers not to place undue reliance on this data. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">All of the information in
this report relates to the situation on September&nbsp;30, 2014, or the quarter ended on that date unless otherwise stated. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Non-IFRS
Financial Information </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">This quarterly financial report contains non-IFRS measures as well as financial data prepared in accordance with
IFRS. We present and discuss the reconciliation of these non-IFRS measures to the respective IFRS measures in the Supplementary Financial Information (Unaudited) section. For more information about non-IFRS measures, see our Web site
www.sap.com/corporate-en/investors/newsandreports/reporting-framework.epx under &#147;Non-IFRS Measures and Estimates.&#148; </FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<TD VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">4</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" ALIGN="right"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">INTERIM MANAGEMENT REPORT</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>ECONOMY AND THE MARKET </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Global Economic Trends </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">After a slow start to the year, the global economy has brightened
since the second quarter of 2014. However, progress has been unsteady and showed variation across the regions, according to the most recent monthly report from the European Central Bank (ECB). The ECB reports that so far, the troubles in Ukraine
have had little effect on the global economy. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">In the Europe, Middle-East, and Africa (EMEA) region, euro area economic output grew moderately
in the first three quarters of 2014. The economies of the largest Central and Eastern Europe countries have recovered since the beginning of the year, but growth there slowed towards the end of the reporting period, the ECB says. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">In the Americas region, the U.S. economy gained new momentum starting in the second quarter after a subdued start to the year, the ECB reports. In
contrast, economic growth in Latin America has weakened since the beginning of the year. In Brazil, among other reasons, decreasing investment spending had a negative impact on growth. Only Mexico showed accelerated growth since the first quarter,
the ECB reports. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Economic trends in the Asia Pacific Japan (APJ) region were again mixed: In Japan, increased consumer spending in
anticipation of rise in value-added tax led to a first-quarter peak in growth and subsequent significant deceleration, the ECB says. Economic growth in China, on the other hand, increased somewhat since the year began. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>The IT Market </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">In the first three
quarters, worldwide IT business growth again outpaced growth in the overall world economy, according to U.S. market research firm International Data Corporation (IDC). Software continued to lead IT spending, with companies investing primarily in the
cloud, in Big Data, social, and mobile. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">IT market growth across the regions was mixed. Notably, IT markets in the emerging economies have
developed at different rates since the beginning of the year, although IDC says they grew more than the IT markets in the industrialized countries. IDC cites the troubles in Ukraine as a factor contributing to the uncertainty of IT markets in the
emerging economies. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The market for IT in the EMEA region has been largely stable but has failed to keep pace with the expansion of the IT
market globally. In Western Europe, IT investment increased modestly but more strongly than in the prior year, IDC reports. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The resurgent
U.S. market drove growth in the Americas region, according to IDC, and IT market expansion was considerably stronger than overall market expansion in the region. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">IT market growth, and particularly software and services segment growth, was much stronger in the AJP region than in the world as a whole. In Japan, IT spending growth was similar to that in the prior
year while in China, IT spending grew more than in the prior year. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Impact on SAP </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">SAP had a solid performance in EMEA, despite uncertainties in the Ukraine and the Middle East. Non-IFRS software and software-related service revenue
increased 8% (8% at constant currencies) with a strong performance in Germany in both software and cloud subscription revenue. Non-IFRS cloud subscriptions and support revenue in EMEA was a particular highlight, growing 59% (59% at constant
currencies), showing exceptional cloud traction in Europe. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The Americas region saw a mixed performance in Latin America. Similar to other
companies in the industry, SAP is seeing a more difficult macro and political environment in Latin America, in particular in Brazil and Argentina, combined with execution issues. Non-IFRS software and software-related service revenue in the Americas
increased 5% (5% at constant currencies). Non-IFRS cloud subscriptions and support revenue grew by 34% (34% at constant currencies). </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The APJ
region had a strong performance with 10% growth in non-IFRS software and software-related service revenue (10% at constant currencies). Non-IFRS cloud subscriptions and support revenue grew by 57% (56% at constant currencies). SAP achieved a
turnaround in its business in Japan with solid double-digit growth. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>VISION, MISSION, AND STRATEGY </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">We did not change our vision, mission, or strategy in the first nine months of 2014. For a detailed description, see the 2013 Integrated Report and item 4
in the 2013 Annual Report on Form 20-F. </FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>PORTFOLIO OF SOFTWARE AND SERVICES </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">In the third quarter of 2014, we made the following enhancements to our portfolio of software and services. For a detailed description of the portfolio of software and services we added in the first half
of 2014, see the half-year report 2014. For a detailed description of our portfolio of software and services, see page 59 and the subsequent pages in our 2013 Integrated Report (www.sapintegratedreport.com) and item 4 in our 2013 Annual Report on
Form 20-F. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Software Portfolio </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">In our 2013 Integrated Report, SAP already stated its commitment to helping customers &#147;simplify everything, so they can do anything.&#148; With SAP
Cloud powered by SAP HANA, we are focusing our simplification on three areas &#150; simplifying our consumption model, simplifying our portfolio, and simplifying the user experience. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">As stated in our report for the first half of 2014, part of this work has been to re-categorize our software products to better reflect our business strategy. We have consolidated our five former market
categories Applications, Analytics, Mobile, Database and Technology, and Cloud into three categories: Applications, Analytics, and Technology Platform. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Applications </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Announced in September, new innovations to SAP solutions for customer
engagement, including the omni-channel hybris platform, SAP Cloud for Sales, SAP Cloud for Service,&nbsp;SAP Cloud for Marketing and SAP Cloud for Social Engagement, enable organizations to drive complete customer engagement. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">In September, SuccessFactors, an SAP company, hosted SuccessConnect 2014, the premier event for human resources (HR) professionals. At the event an
expanded vision for SuccessFactors Learning, which includes the release of quick guides and programs capabilities, and partnerships to help companies close the skills gap was announced. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">SAP participated in Super Mobility Week powered by CTIA, which also took place in September. Our announcements at this event included: </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Launch of augmented reality apps including the SAP AR Warehouse Picker mobile app and SAP AR Service Technician mobile app, which help simplify and
improve user experience and work processes. </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Line-of-business mobile apps from SAP including the SAP Work Manager, SAP CRM Service Manager and SAP Inventory Manager mobile apps that are tested and
able to run on the new tablet from Samsung launched in September. </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

<TR>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Support for customers running the latest mobile operating system and iPhone 6 from Apple with the latest versions of SAP Mobile Platform, SAP Mobile
Secure portfolio and mobile apps from SAP. </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">We announced the availability of SAP Supply Chain Orchestration, cloud edition,
which integrates the SAP Supply Network Collaboration application and Ariba Collaborative Supply Chain. Combined, they provide visibility into supply side trading partners and a single interface for managing the advanced supply chain needs of
critical, high-value partners. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">As the official global technology partner of the 2015 Solheim Cup, we unveiled a new mobile app for fan
engagement powered by the SAP HANA Cloud Platform. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Version 2.0 of the SAP Demand Signal Management application became generally available in
July. Powered by SAP HANA, the latest version helps increase market and demand visibility as well as responsiveness. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">SAP ERP Foundation
Extension package and SAP Customer Relationship Management (SAP CRM) powered by SAP HANA were made available for 30-day cloud-based trials. Based on SAP Rapid Deployment solutions, the trials include best practices and sample data. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The new cloud&#150;based SAP Integrated Business Planning solution comprises SAP Integrated Business Planning for sales and operations, SAP Integrated
Business Planning for inventory, SAP Integrated Business Planning for supply and SAP Supply Chain Control Tower to deliver analysis and share alerts of real-time information across the end-to-end supply and demand network. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Now generally available, SAP Innovation Management powered by SAP HANA manages ideation with innovative technology to help companies overcome
departmental silos and drive innovation. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Announced in July, the expansion of the SAP Mobile Secure portfolio with the addition of mobile
application management which now makes it easier for companies to simply and proactively push their mobile apps into the hands of employees, business partners and consumers. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">At the beginning of the third quarter, SAP announced four new user experience (UX) rapid-deployment solutions that enable businesses to adopt the latest user UX innovations from SAP, including SAP Fiori
and SAP Screen Personas software. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><I>Industry Recognition </I></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">SAP was named a leader in &#147;The Forrester Wave: Customer-Centric Global Banking Platforms, Q3 2014.&#148; </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">ARC Advisory Group named SAP as the market leader in transportation management systems (TMS) and a market leader in warehouse management systems (WMS). </FONT></P>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Analytics </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Updates to SAP Lumira software and the SAP InfiniteInsight solution announced in September help provide better data analysis support. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">A joint initiative with Panasonic intends to co-innovate in the area of video-based sports analytics by integrating the Panasonic video and tracking software with the SAP Match Insights solution, an
analytics prototype SAP developed with the German Football Association (DFB) for the soccer world championship 2014 in Brazil. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">SAP announced
in August that we are the FC Bayern Munich AG official partner for sport analytics and enterprise software. Over the next three years we will work together on innovative solutions to support the club&#146;s goals to further expand its global
presence, maximize the team&#146;s performance and enhance the experience for fans. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">In July, we announced integration of the SAP
InfiniteInsight solution with the SAP Customer Engagement Intelligence solution powered by SAP HANA to help companies increase the efficiency and effectiveness of their marketing, sales and service organizations. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The general availability of the SAP Audit Management application powered by SAP HANA, which helps streamline audit processes with an alternative to
spreadsheets and manual tools. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><I>Industry Recognition </I></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">SAP was ranked as a leader in &#147;The Forrester Wave: Agile Business Intelligence Platforms, Q3 2014&#148;. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">SAP was also recognized as a leader in the &#147;Ovum Decision Matrix: Selecting a Business Intelligence Solution, 2014 &#150; 2015&#148;. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The SAP Audit Management application powered by SAP HANA was presented the Ventana Research Overall Technology Innovation Award for its ability to improve productivity and outcomes for businesses across
various industries. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Technology Platform </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Our Technology Platform category addresses the database, IT management, cloud infrastructure, and mobile platform segments of the market. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">New updates to SAP solutions for enterprise information management (EIM) announced in September help customers simplify big data. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">SAP and Esri, an international supplier of Geographic Information System (GIS) software, web GIS and geodatabase management applications partnered to make available new innovations, features and
functionalities across the SAP HANA platform, analytics, mobile and business applications that will help strengthen and simplify integration with Esri&#146;s geospatial services and content. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">New open source partnerships with Cloud Foundry and the OpenStack Foundation are a significant step in our strategy to provide an open technology platform and deepen our commitment to the developer
community. In addition, we announced new cloud-based developer tools SAP HANA Answers and SAP River Rapid Development Environment. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Four new,
free massive open online courses (MOOCs) focused on the SAP Fiori user experience and the SAP HANA platform were announced in August. The new courses aim to provide professionals, students and the general public the most up-to-date knowledge needed
to build competitive skill sets in the marketplace. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">SAP announced a co-innovation project with Toyota InfoTechnology Center USA (Toyota ITC)
and VeriFone, a provider of technology for electronic payment transactions, that will help simplify drivers&#146; fueling experience. Built on SAP HANA Cloud Platform, the solution will aggregate information on a vehicle&#146;s location, route and
fuel level as well as points of interest. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><I>Industry Recognition </I></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">SAP was rated a leader in the &#147;The Forrester Wave&#153;: Big Data Streaming Analytics Platforms, Q3 2014.&#148; </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">For the seventh consecutive year, Gartner has named SAP a leader in the &#147;Magic Quadrant for Data Integration Tools&#148; 2014 report. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Gartner positioned SAP in the leader quadrant of the &#147;Magic Quadrant for Mobile Application Development Platforms (MADP)&#148; 2014 report and the &#147;Magic Quadrant 2014 report for on-premises
application integration suites&#148;. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The SAP Mobile Secure Portfolio has been positioned by independent analyst firm Ovum as a market leader
in the 2014 Ovum Decision Matrix for Enterprise Mobility Management (EMM). </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Ventana Research announced SAP customer, Varian Medical Systems, a
leading creator of cancer treatment technology, as the winner of the Service and Supply Chain Leadership Award for utilizing SAP Business Suite powered by SAP HANA software. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>RESEARCH AND DEVELOPMENT </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Our total research and development expense decreased slightly to
&#128;1,661&nbsp;million in the first nine months of 2014, compared to &#128;1,676&nbsp;million in the corresponding period in 2013. We had 18,322 full-time equivalent (FTE) employees working in research and development teams on September&nbsp;30,
2014, which increased by 604 FTEs compared to the prior year (September 30, 2013: 17,718). </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">On our IFRS numbers, the portion of total revenue
we spent on research and development in the first nine months of 2014 was 13.7%, which decreased by 0.6 percentage points compared to the 14.3% recorded for the first nine </FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" ALIGN="center">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">
months of 2013. On the non-IFRS numbers, the portion of total revenue we spent on R&amp;D in the first nine months of 2014 was 13.1%, which decreased by 0.5 percentage points compared to the same
period in the previous year (13.6%). </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>ACQUISITIONS </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">SAP and the US-based company Concur, the leader in the multi-billion space for travel and expense management software, announced on September&nbsp;18, 2014, that they have entered into an agreement to
acquire Concur by SAP. Concur has more than 23,000 customers, 4,200 employees and 25&nbsp;million active users in over 150 countries. With Concur, SAP&#146;s business network &#150; the world&#146;s largest &#150; will transact more than US$600
billion annually, deliver frictionless commerce across more than 25 different industries and address annual corporate travel spend of US$1.2 trillion worldwide. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The Concur board of directors has unanimously approved the transaction, which is expected to close in the fourth quarter 2014 or the first quarter 2015, subject to Concur stockholder approval, clearances
by the relevant regulatory authorities, and other customary closing conditions. The per-share purchase price of US$129 represents a 20% premium over the September&nbsp;17, 2014, closing price and an enterprise value of approximately US$8.3 billion.
</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">In addition, SAP acquired SeeWhy and Fieldglass in May and June, 2014. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">For more information about acquisitions in the first half of 2014, see our half-year report 2014. For more information about acquisitions in the prior year, see Note (4)&nbsp;in the Notes to the 2013
Annual Report. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>EMPLOYEES </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Nothing has a greater impact on SAP&#146;s long-term success than the creativity, talent, and commitment of our people. Their ability to understand the
needs of our customers and to innovate delivers sustainable value to our company, our customers, and society. Successful strategies to attract, retain, develop, and engage our employees, therefore, are critical to driving a culture of innovation,
sustained growth, and profitability. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">An important factor for our long-term success is our ability to attract and retain talented employees.
In the third quarter of 2014, the employee retention rate was 93.3% (compared to 93.6% in the second quarter of 2013). We define employee retention rate as the ratio between the average number of employees less voluntary employee departures
(fluctuation) and the average number of employees (in full-time equivalents). </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">One of SAP&#146;s overall non-financial goals is fostering a
diverse workforce, specifically increasing the number of women in management. At the end of the third quarter of 2014, 21.3% of all management positions at SAP were held by women, compared to 21.0% at the end of September 2013. SAP has set a
long-term target to increase the share of women in management to 25% by the year 2017. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">On September&nbsp;30, 2014, we had 68,835 full-time
equivalent (FTE) employees worldwide (September 30, 2013: 66,061;&nbsp;December&nbsp;31, 2013: 66,572). </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Those headcount numbers included
17,343 FTEs based in Germany (September 30, 2013: 16,934), and 13,395 FTEs based in the United States (September 30, 2013: 13,503). </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>ORGANIZATION AND CHANGES IN MANAGEMENT </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">For information about changes in the first half of 2014, see the half-year report 2014. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Effective July&nbsp;1, 2014, Luka Mucic succeeded Werner Brandt as Chief Financial Officer, who withdrew, as planned, from the Executive Board. </FONT></P>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>REPORT ON ECONOMIC POSITION </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">We simplified the presentation of our software and software-related service revenue in our income statement starting with the first quarter of 2014 to express our focus on the combined power of our fast
growing cloud business and our solid core business. With this modification, only the order and subtotals were changed; the content of line items remained unchanged. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Software and software-related service revenue now starts with the line item cloud subscriptions and support and is followed by line items software and support of our on-premise activities. The software
and cloud subscriptions row was deleted and a new sum for software and support was added. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">In the discussion of our assets, financial
position, and operating results, the financial data presented for the first nine months of 2014 fully contains the revenue and expenses, assets, liabilities and cash flow from hybris. Fieldglass numbers are included in our consolidated financial
statements since the May&nbsp;2, 2014 acquisition date. hybris numbers are included on a pro rata basis in the prior-year amounts &#150; hybris was acquired on August&nbsp;1, 2013. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Segment Information </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">In the first quarter of 2014, we took significant steps to drive
forward our strategy and our ambition to become THE cloud company powered by SAP HANA. To execute this strategy, we merged certain areas of the company that performed similar tasks (for example, the on-premise sales forces with the cloud sales
forces, and the on-premise support units with the cloud support units) to achieve a seamless organization of SAP. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Since this integration, our
cloud-related activities are no longer dealt with by separate components in our Company. Our Executive Board assesses the financial performance of our Company on an integrated basis only. Consequently, with effect from the first quarter of 2014, SAP
has one single operating segment. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">For more information about the changes to our segment reporting, see the Notes to the Consolidated Interim
Financial Statements section, Note (19). </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Performance Against Our Outlook for 2014 (Non-IFRS) </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">In this section, all discussion of the first nine months&#146; contribution to target achievement is based exclusively on non-IFRS measures. However, in
the following section, the discussion of results refers to IFRS figures only, so those figures are not expressly identified as IFRS figures. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Starting in the second quarter of 2014, we additionally adjust our non-IFRS operating expense by excluding the expenses resulting from the Versata
litigation (for more information about this litigation, see the Notes to the Consolidated Interim Financial Statements section, Note (16)). Prior-year amounts have been adjusted accordingly. We exclude the Versata litigation expenses to provide
additional insight into the comparability of our ongoing operating performance across periods and to continue the alignment of our non-IFRS measures with our internal performance measures. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">We present, discuss, and explain the reconciliation from IFRS measures to non-IFRS measures in the Supplementary Financial Information (Unaudited) section. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Guidance for 2014 (Non-IFRS) </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">For our
guidance based on non-IFRS numbers, see the Forecast for SAP passage in this interim management report. </FONT></P>

</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Actual Performance in the Third Quarter of 2014 (Non-IFRS) </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Our revenue from cloud subscriptions and support (non-IFRS) was &#128;278&nbsp;million (Q3 2013: &#128;197&nbsp;million), an increase of 41% (42% at
constant currencies) compared to the same period in 2013. Our cloud subscriptions and support margin was down 11.1 percentage points to 60%. This decrease was primarily due to increasing expenses related to the ramp-up of the cloud business, with
related investments, as well as additional personnel expenses to support the growth of our SAP HANA Enterprise Cloud offerings. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Deferred
cloud subscriptions and support revenue (non-IFRS) was &#128;498&nbsp;million on September&nbsp;30, 2014 (September 30, 2013: &#128;382&nbsp;million), an increase of 30%. On a constant currency basis, the increase was 22%. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Our annual cloud revenue run rate (non-IFRS) is &#128;1,334&nbsp;million. The annual revenue run rate is the total of third-quarter 2014 cloud
subscription and support revenue (non-IFRS) (&#128;278&nbsp;million)&nbsp;plus non-IFRS cloud-related professional services and other service revenue (&#128;55&nbsp;million)&nbsp;multiplied by four. This definition has changed from the previous
year. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Calculated cloud billings (non-IFRS) increased 51% year-over-year. On a constant currency basis, the increase was 27%. This is
calculated as total of a period&#146;s cloud subscription and support revenue and of the respective period&#146;s change in the deferred cloud subscription and support revenue balance. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">SAP continues to expand the world&#146;s largest Web-based business trading community, with trailing twelve month spend volume on our Ariba network with close to US$600&nbsp;billion (compared to the same
period in 2013 at approximately US$500&nbsp;billion). </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">In the third quarter of 2014, software and software-related service revenue (non-IFRS)
was &#128;3,601&nbsp;million (Q3 2013: &#128;3,363&nbsp;million), an increase of 7%. On a constant currency basis, the increase was 7%. SAP&#146;s hybris omni-channel e-commerce platform in combination with Cloud for Sales had another quarter of
triple-digit growth in software revenue and cloud subscriptions and support revenue (non-IFRS). In addition, the revenue share from more predictable cloud and support revenue (non-IFRS) increased to 62% (Q3 2013: 59%). </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Non-IFRS total revenue in the same period was &#128;4,256&nbsp;million (Q3 2013: &#128;4,057&nbsp;million), an increase of 5%. On a constant currency
basis, the increase was 5%. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Non-IFRS operating expense in the third quarter of 2014 was &#128;2,901&nbsp;million, an increase of 5%
(Q3&nbsp;2013: &#128;2,761&nbsp;million). On a constant currency basis, non-IFRS operating expense increased by 6%. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Non-IFRS operating profit
was &#128;1,355&nbsp;million (Q3 2013: &#128;1,296&nbsp;million), an increase of 5% (3% at constant currencies). </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Non-IFRS operating margin in
the third quarter of 2014 was 31.8%, a decrease of 0.1 percentage points (Q3 2013: 32.0%). Non-IFRS operating margin on a constant currency basis was 31.5%, a decrease of 0.5 percentage points. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">In the third quarter of 2014, non-IFRS profit after tax was &#128;1,010&nbsp;million (Q3 2013: &#128;933&nbsp;million), an increase of 8%. Non-IFRS basic
earnings per share was &#128;0.84 (Q3 2013: &#128;0.78), an increase of 8%. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The non-IFRS effective tax rate in the third quarter of 2014 was
27.7% (Q3 2013: 27.6%). </FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<TD NOWRAP VALIGN="bottom"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Actual Performance in the First Nine Months of 2014 (Non-IFRS) </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">In the first nine months of 2014, our revenue from cloud subscriptions and support (non-IFRS) was &#128;741&nbsp;million (first nine months of 2013:
&#128;547&nbsp;million), an increase of 35% (40% at constant currencies) compared to the same period in 2013. Our cloud subscriptions and support margin was down 7.6 percentage points to 65%. This decrease was primarily due to increasing expenses
related to the ramp-up of the cloud business, with related investments, as well as additional personnel expenses to support the growth of our SAP HANA Enterprise Cloud offerings. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">In the first nine months of 2014, software and software-related service revenue (non-IFRS) was &#128;10,139&nbsp;million (first nine months of 2013: &#128;9,647&nbsp;million), an increase of 5%. On a
constant currency basis, the increase was 8%. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Non-IFRS total revenue in the same period was &#128;12,110&nbsp;million (first nine months of
2013: &#128;11,784&nbsp;million), an increase of 3%. On a constant currency basis, the increase was 5%. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Our prior-year non-IFRS operating
expense, operating profit, operating margin, and profit after tax have been adjusted for the Versata litigation expenses to comply with the modified set of non-IFRS adjustments. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Non-IFRS operating expense in the first nine months of 2014 was &#128;8,600&nbsp;million (first nine months of 2013: &#128;8,400&nbsp;million), an increase of 2%. On a constant currency basis, the
increase was 5%. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Non-IFRS operating profit was &#128;3,510&nbsp;million (first nine months of 2013: &#128;3,385&nbsp;million), an increase of
4% (6% at constant currencies). </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Non-IFRS operating margin in the first nine months of 2014 was 29.0%, an increase of 0.3 percentage points
(first nine months of 2013: 28.7%). Non-IFRS operating margin on a constant currency basis was 28.8%, an increase of 0.1 percentage points. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">In the first nine months of 2014, non-IFRS profit after tax was &#128;2,615&nbsp;million (first nine months of 2013: &#128;2,474&nbsp;million), an
increase of 6%. Non-IFRS basic earnings per share was &#128;2.19 (first nine months of 2013: &#128;2.08), an increase of 6%. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The non-IFRS
effective tax rate in the first nine months of 2014 was 26.4% (first nine months of 2013: 25.6%). The year-over-year increase in the effective tax rate mainly resulted from changes in taxes for prior years and in the regional allocation of income
which were partly compensated by tax effects relating to intercompany financing and changes in foreign currency exchange rates. </FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>OPERATING RESULTS IN THE THIRD QUARTER (IFRS) </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Orders </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The total number of completed transactions for on-premise software in the third
quarter of 2014 decreased 2% year-over-year to 12,544 (Q3 2013: 12,774). In addition, the average value of software orders received for on-premise software deals decreased 1% compared to the year before. Of all our software orders received in the
third quarter of 2014, 27% were attributable to deals worth more than &#128;5&nbsp;million (Q3 2013: 32%), while 44% were attributable to deals worth less than &#128;1&nbsp;million (Q3&nbsp;2013: 41%). </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Revenue </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Our revenue from cloud
subscriptions and support was &#128;277&nbsp;million (Q3 2013: &#128;191&nbsp;million), an increase of 45% compared to the same period in 2013. Deferred cloud subscriptions and support revenue was &#128;498&nbsp;million on September&nbsp;30, 2014
(September 30, 2013: &#128;376&nbsp;million). </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Our annual cloud revenue run rate is &#128;1,330&nbsp;million. Calculated cloud billings
increased 55% year-over-year. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">In the third quarter of 2014, software revenue was &#128;951&nbsp;million (Q3 2013: &#128;975&nbsp;million), a
decrease of 2% compared to the same period in 2013. The revenue share from predictable cloud and support revenue increased to 62% (Q3 2013: 59%). </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Total revenue was &#128;4,254&nbsp;million (Q3 2013: &#128;4,045&nbsp;million), an increase of 5% compared to the same period in 2013. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Operating Expense </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">In the third quarter of 2014, our operating expense increased 3% to
&#128;3,097&nbsp;million (Q3 2013: &#128;3,003&nbsp;million). </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Operating Profit and Operating Margin </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">In the third quarter of 2014, operating profit increased 11% compared with the same period in the previous year to &#128;1,157&nbsp;million (Q3 2013:
&#128;1,043&nbsp;million). This increase is primarily due to a reduction in our share-based payments expense based on our revised expectation of performance against targets in alignment with a changed outlook. Our operating margin increased by 1.4
percentage points to 27.2% (Q3 2013: 25.8%). </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Profit After Tax and Earnings per Share </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">In the third quarter of 2014, profit after tax was &#128;881&nbsp;million (Q3 2013: &#128;762 million), an increase of 16%. Basic earnings per share was
&#128;0.74 (Q3 2013: &#128;0.64), an increase of 15%. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The effective tax rate in the third quarter of 2014 was 26.5% (Q3 2013: 26.4%).
</FONT></P>

</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>OPERATING RESULTS IN THE FIRST NINE MONTHS (IFRS) </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Orders </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The total number of on-premise software deals we closed decreased by 3% from the
comparator amount in the first nine months of 2014 to 37,628 (first nine months of 2013: 38,697). In contrast, the average value of on-premise software orders we received remained stable compared with the previous year. In the first nine months of
2014, 22% (first nine months of 2013: 23%) of the value of new software orders came from orders whose volume exceeded &#128;5&nbsp;million, while 47% (first nine months of 2013: 46%) came from orders worth less than &#128;1&nbsp;million. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Revenue </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Our revenue from cloud
subscriptions and support was &#128;738&nbsp;million (first nine months of 2013: &#128;488&nbsp;million), an increase of 51% compared to the same period in 2013. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">In the first nine months of 2014, software revenue was &#128;2,532&nbsp;million (first nine months of 2013: &#128;2,614&nbsp;million), a decrease of 3% compared to the same period in 2013. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Total revenue was &#128;12,103&nbsp;million (first nine months of 2013: &#128;11,708&nbsp;million), an increase of 3% compared to the same period in
2013. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Operating Expense </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">In
the first nine months of 2014, our operating expense increased by 5% to &#128;9,525&nbsp;million (first nine months of 2013: &#128;9,031 million). A main driver of this increase were the expenses for the TomorrowNow and Versata litigations in the
amount of &#128;307&nbsp;million (first nine months of 2013: positive effect of &#128;32&nbsp;million). For more information about these litigations, see the Notes to the Interim Financial Statements section, Note (16). </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Operating Profit and Operating Margin </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">In the first nine months of 2014, compared with the same period in the previous year, operating profit decreased by 4% to &#128;2,578&nbsp;million (first
nine months of 2013: &#128;2,677&nbsp;million). The decrease was mainly due to the expenses for the TomorrowNow and Versata litigations. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Our
operating margin decreased by 1.6 percentage points to 21.3% (first nine months of 2013: 22.9%). The expenses for the TomorrowNow and Versata litigations had a 2.5 percentage point negative effect on our operating margin in the first nine months of
2014 (first nine months of 2013: 0.3 percentage point positive effect). </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Profit After Tax and Earnings per Share </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">In the first nine months of 2014, profit after tax was &#128;1,971&nbsp;million (first nine months of 2013: &#128;2,006&nbsp;million), a decrease of 2%.
Basic earnings per share was &#128;1.65 (first nine months of 2013: &#128;1.68), a decrease of 2%. The year-over-year decrease was mainly driven by the expenses for the TomorrowNow and Versata litigations. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The effective tax rate in the first nine months of 2014 was 24.8% (first nine months of 2013: 23.4%). The year-over-year increase in the effective tax
rate mainly resulted from changes in taxes for prior years and in the regional allocation of income which were partly compensated by tax effects relating to intercompany financing and changes in foreign currency exchange rates </FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<TD VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">INTERIM REPORT JANUARY &#150; SEPTEMBER 2014</FONT></TD>

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>FINANCES (IFRS) </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Capital Structure Management </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">After undergoing an external credit rating process, on
September&nbsp;19, 2014, SAP SE was assigned a first-time long-term issuer credit rating of &#147;A2&#148; by Moody&#146;s and &#147;A&#148; by Standard&nbsp;&amp; Poor&#146;s, both with outlook &#147;Stable&#148;. The ratings incorporate an
additional credit facility of up to &#128;7bn for the expected acquisition of Concur. Such credit facility should cover payments of the purchase price and related transaction costs as well as debt refinancing of Concur. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Based on the strong financial profile, track record of fast debt repayments and proactive liquidity management, SAP has established a very strong
reputation with debt investors.While SAP has continuously realized successful financing transactions at attractive terms, an external rating provides SAP with the opportunity to broaden investor access and to optimally benefit from its high
creditworthiness. An external rating provides investors, customers and suppliers with an independent view of SAP&#146;s strength and stability. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Cash Flow and Liquidity </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Operating cash
flow for the first nine month of 2014 was &#128;3,082&nbsp;million (first nine month of 2013: &#128;3,040 million). Thus, despite the payment from the Versata-litigation, our operating cash flow increased 1% over the same period in the previous
year. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Group liquidity stood at &#128;3,403&nbsp;million on September&nbsp;30, 2014 (December 31, 2013: &#128;2,841&nbsp;million). Group
liquidity comprised cash and cash equivalents totaling &#128;3,354&nbsp;million (December 31, 2013: &#128;2,748&nbsp;million) and current investments totaling &#128;49&nbsp;million (December 31, 2013: &#128;93 million). </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Group Liquidity of SAP Group </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Days&#146; sales outstanding (DSO) for receivables, defined as average number of days from the raised invoice to cash
receipt from the customer, was 65&nbsp;days, a 3-day increase year over year. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>ASSETS (IFRS) </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Analysis of Consolidated Statements of Financial Position </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The total assets of the Group were &#128;29,593&nbsp;million on September&nbsp;30, 2014, an increase of &#128;2,502&nbsp;million since December&nbsp;31, 2013, resulting mainly from an increase in goodwill
out of the Fieldglass acquisition as well as foreign exchange related revaluations. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The equity ratio on September&nbsp;30, 2014, was 60%
(December 31, 2013: 59%), a slight increase. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Investments </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Investments in intangible assets and property, plant, and equipment were &#128;1,224&nbsp;million in the first nine months of 2014, which decreased by &#128;409&nbsp;million compared to the first nine
months of 2013 (&#128;1,633 million), which is mainly due to the hybris acquisition of the prior year. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Off-Balance-Sheet Financial
Instruments </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">There are no off-balance-sheet financial instruments, such as sale-and-lease-back transactions, asset-backed securities, or
liabilities related to structured entities, that are not disclosed in our interim Consolidated Financial Statements. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Competitive
Intangibles </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The assets that are the basis for our current and future success do not appear on the Consolidated Statements of Financial
Position. This is apparent from a comparison of </FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" ALIGN="center">

<TR>
<TD WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="96%"></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">14</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" ALIGN="right"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">INTERIM MANAGEMENT REPORT</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">
the market capitalization of SAP SE, which was &#128;70.1 billion, with the equity of the SAP Group on the Consolidated Statements of Financial Position, which was &#128;17.7 billion on
September&nbsp;30, 2014 (December 31, 2013: &#128;16.0&nbsp;billion). This means that the market capitalization of our equity is almost four times higher than the book value. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Customer capital, our employees and their knowledge and skills, our ecosystem of partners, the SAP brand, and our past investments in research and development are some of the most important competitive
intangibles that influence our market value. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">According to the 2014 Interbrand annual survey of the Top 100 Best Global Brands, SAP is ranked
the 25th most valued brand in the world. Interbrand determined a value of US$17.3 billion. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>ENERGY CONSUMPTION AND GREENHOUSE GAS EMISSIONS
</B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Over the past several years, we have worked to better understand the connections between our energy consumption, its related cost, and the
resulting environmental impact. Today we measure and address our energy usage throughout SAP, as well as our greenhouse gas emissions across our entire value chain. Between the beginning of 2008 and the end of the third quarter 2014, we calculate
that energy efficiency initiatives have contributed to a cumulative cost avoidance of &#128;300&nbsp;million, compared to a business-as-usual extrapolation. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Moreover, to credibly offer solutions that help our customers better manage their use of resources, we must do so ourselves. By addressing the financial and environmental impact of our energy consumption,
we gain valuable insights to create solutions for our customers. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Our goal is to reduce the greenhouse gas (GHG) emissions from our operations
to levels of the year 2000 by 2020. SAP&#146;s GHG emissions for the third quarter 2014 totaled 125 kilotons compared to 135&nbsp;kilotons in the third quarter of 2013. This decrease is primarily due to additional renewable energy certificates
procured. Despite emissions reductions compared to 2013, there is a risk that we might not meet our year-end emissions target of 440 kilotons. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">As we measure our emissions per employee and per euro of revenue, we gain insight into our efficiency as we grow. Since 2007, we have increased our
efficiency according to both measures, lowering our emissions per employee by about 46% and per euro of revenue by about 32% at the end of September 2014 (rolling four quarters). </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Since July, private users have the possibility to use TwoGo by SAP (www.twogo.com) for ridesharing. Private use is free of charge. The main benefit of TwoGo by SAP is to organize regular short distance
rides, e.g. for commuters. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">In recognition of the exemplary actions SAP has taken to embed sustainability across its business worldwide, SAP
has been ranked the most sustainable software company in the Dow Jones Sustainability Indexes for the eighth consecutive year. In addition, SAP has been recognized as one the top 100 green power users by the U.S. Environmental Protection Agency
(EPA). </FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>SAP STOCK </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">SAP SE common stock is listed on the Frankfurt Stock Exchange as well as on a number of other German exchanges. On the New York Stock Exchange (NYSE), SAP American depositary receipts (ADRs), each
representing one common share, trade under the symbol SAP. SAP is a component of the DAX (the index of 30 German blue chip companies) and the Dow Jones EURO STOXX 50. We use the S&amp;P North American Technology Software Index for comparison
purposes. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Key Facts About SAP Stock / SAP ADRs </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
